<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-06-08T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-06-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="319" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d319">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">493.11 N 15/163: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-06-08T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">June 8,
                                        1928—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>185. Your 418, June 3, 11 a.m.</p>
                        <list>
                            <label>1.</label>
                            <item>Department approves your suggestions <hi rend="italic">in
                                    toto</hi> as guiding initial instructions. However, Department
                                feels that before the termination of the life of the Commission all
                                claims for real property losses <pb facs="0466" n="348" xml:id="pg_348"/> should be examined, be appraised and, if it
                                proves possible, be acted upon.</item>
                            <label>2.</label>
                            <item>Reference to paragraph 4. Dr. Wu<note n="32" xml:id="d319fn32">C.
                                    C. Wu, Special Representative of the Chinese Nationalist
                                    Government.</note> has confidentially informed Department that
                                he has cabled Nanking urging prompt restoration.</item>
                        </list>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>